ssh-alertd (0.1.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add GitHub Actions release automation (.deb amd64/arm64 + standalone
    tarballs published to the GitHub Release). No runtime changes.

 -- Amekiri Studio <info@amekiri.com>  Fri, 26 Jun 2026 12:00:00 +0000

ssh-alertd (0.1.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Reliably chown the config to the ssh-alertd user on install: run
    systemd-sysusers/systemd-tmpfiles explicitly in postinst and add a chown
    fallback, so the daemon can read its token regardless of hook timing.

 -- Amekiri Studio <info@amekiri.com>  Fri, 26 Jun 2026 11:40:00 +0000

ssh-alertd (0.1.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Run as a dedicated "ssh-alertd" system user (sysusers.d) instead of
    DynamicUser, and grant it ownership of the config (tmpfiles.d) so the
    daemon can read its token. Fixes a startup failure with permission denied
    on /etc/ssh-alertd/config.json.

 -- Amekiri Studio <info@amekiri.com>  Fri, 26 Jun 2026 11:30:00 +0000

ssh-alertd (0.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release: modular SSH login alert daemon with Telegram notifier.

